@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Blokator" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any block located at the uppermost part of the
game board, this will make it fall towards the bottom of the board.
If a block is already under or beside the fallen block and both
blocks are of the same type and/or colour, they will be briefly
'highlighted' but will remain on the board.

  Arrows, located on either side of the uppermost blocks, move
blocks in the direction the arrows are pointing. If a block is
located on an edge of the board it will go to the other edge. One
thing to remember: clicking on either arrows will sometimes make a
random block to fall. As the game progress, the probability of a
block falling will happen more frequently, so better watch out!

  Unless when a block fell randomly, you get points for each pair
of blocks that are matched, in the following way:

  blocks of the same colour:                       1 point
  blocks of the same type but of different colour: 5 points
  blocks of the same type and colour:              20 points

  When no more blocks can be added on the board, all the matched
blocks will be removed and the remaining blocks, if there are any,
will remain right where they are. This may complicate the game a
little, especially if they are at the highest positions on the
board. If new blocks of the same type and/or colour are placed next
to those blocks, then they will be removed later on...

  The game ends when no blocks can be added to the board and no
blocks are already matched.

  Have fun!

